The paper deals with facial expression recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of feature extraction and selection methods also suggests a machine learning approach, which falls under the categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of discriminative information for facial expression recognition, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
